                        <h3>Understanding Your Boiler</h3>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_13" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What is a system boiler?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_13" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>System boilers heat your radiators directly and they usually store hot water in a storage
                                        cylinder. These are commonly located in either an airing cupboard or in a garage.
                                        They heat a large volume of water at once and then store this hot water until you
                                        decide to use it. They are less efficient than combi boilers, which only heat the
                                        water you need, when you need it.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_13_1" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What is a standard boiler?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_13_1" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>Also known as conventional boiler, the standard boiler stores hot water in a storage
                                        cylinder, similar to system boilers, but the difference is that a standard boiler
                                        is fed by a separate coldwater tank – commonly found in the loft. There's another
                                        separate tank, called a ‘feed and expansion cistern', usually in the loft too. Standard
                                        boilers are the largest type of boiler and so are not generally suitable for smaller
                                        living spaces.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_14" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What is an ERP boiler?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_14" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>The ‘ERP’ – Energy related products label will tell you how efficiently your boiler (or
                                        any other appliance like a fridge or a washing machine) uses energy. It's designed
                                        to help you choose the right appliance and is designed to ensure you save the most
                                        money on your heating and energy bills. The ERP label will rate an appliance from
                                        A+++ to G.</p>
                                    <p>A+++ is the most efficient boiler you can get.</p>
                                    <p>It also tells you how loud the appliance is in decibels and how much heat it outputs
                                        in kilowatts.</p>
                                    <p>All of the boilers available to you on the 24|7 Staywarm packages are rated A for efficiency.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
