                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_15" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>In most cases, this is highly tricky. There is usually a huge cost associated with hiring
                                        specialist equipment that lets our engineers reach the outside of your home above
                                        the second floor and we don't want to have to pass that cost on to you. If you live
                                        above the second floor, please contact our customer service team and we’ll discuss
                                        any viable options with you.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_16" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What is a combi boiler? Is it better?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_16" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>Combi boilers, or ‘combination boilers’ as they are known are the most popular type of
                                        boiler in the UK. In fact, they’re so popular that they’re used by 74% of households
                                        across the country! </p>
                                    <p>They're named ‘combination' because they combine both a high-efficiency water heater
                                        and a central heating boiler all in one simple package and they are highly efficient.
                                        Also, combi boilers can save you lots of money on your heating bills so they’re a
                                        great option for those looking to save some money.</p>
                                    <p>That's because:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>They heat the water only when you need it, rather than storing hot water up like
                                            traditional boilers</li>
                                        <li>They're small and compact, as they don't use an external hot water tank so are great
                                            for those living in apartments or for those with limited space.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_17" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What are thermostatic radiator valves (TRV’s)? Do I need them?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_17" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>Thermostatic radiator valves – or TRVs as they’re most commonly known – are controls
                                        for your radiators. They regulate how much hot water flows into the radiator so you
                                        can adjust its temperature. If you’d rather have it hotter in one room than another,
                                        simply alter the dial accordingly.</p>
                                    <p>TRVs also let you turn some radiators off (for Nine, in a room you're not using) without
                                        completely turning the heating off.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>Why do I need TRVs?</b>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>The Government recommends that every household has thermostatic radiator valves because
                                        they:
                                    </p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Save you money on heating bills</li>
                                        <li>Use less energy</li>
                                        <li>Are more energy efficient and are better for the environmen</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>But they're not mandatory, so if you don’t have them don’t worry too much. TRV’s simply
                                        give you more control over your home heating.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>How much do they cost?</b>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>Each individual valve costs £35. If you don't have them already installed in your home,
                                        we can include them in your package and install them for you. You'll get one for
                                        each bedroom, meaning you’ll never have to wake up to a cold house again!</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>What if I want TRV’S for other rooms too?</b>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>You can change the number of TRVs you receive before you complete your purchase, so if
                                        this is the case, just let us know! </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>What if I don’t want any TRV’s installed?</b>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>Not a problem at all! Just make sure you remove them from your boiler package before
                                        you purchase or speak to one of our friendly advisors. </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_18" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What is a flue?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_18" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>A flue is a pipe, almost like a chimney, that carries waste from the boiler to the outside.
                                        You can see your flue exit (the part of the flue that comes out of your house) on
                                        the outside wall or roof of your home.</p>
                                    <p>Flues can either be round or square depending on the home that you live in.</p>
                                    <p>If the flue is less than two metres off the ground, or if it’s underneath a car park
                                        or shelter, it'll be covered by a guard. It will include a piece of wire mesh that
                                        surrounds the flue.</p>
                                    <p>When you buy a boiler from 24|7 Staywarm, we'll supply and fit a brand new flue for you,
                                        along with all the safety attachments you need, so you don’t need to worry about
                                        any part of your central heating system.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_19" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        When is my installation date booked?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_19" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>Your installation will be booked as soon as you’ve signed your order contract or paid
                                        the whole balance in full. You’ll then be given a list of available dates to perform
                                        the installation that are suitable for you.</p>
                                    <p>If you haven’t completed the payment or paid the deposit required within 24 hours after
                                        choosing your installation date, the slots may become available to other customers
                                        so it’s crucial you do this as soon as possible</p>
                                    <p>If you’ve chosen next-day installation:</p>
                                    <p>Finish your payment option or sign your finance agreement before 3.30pm to guarantee
                                        your next day installation slot.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_20" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        Will you do a chemical flush?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_20" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>Of course! Before we install any new boiler or central heating system, we always do a
                                        chemical flush, which is essentially a hot flush and dose.</p>
                                    <p>One of our highly skilled engineers will put a cleaner into your system, flushing it
                                        out through the boiler. Any debris will be caught by the approved 24|7 Staywarm magnetic
                                        filter. </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_20_1" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        Will you perform a power flush?

                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_20_1" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>After years of experience performing power flushes, we've found that performing a powerflush
                                        on an old system simply causes more problems and can potentially affect the efficiency
                                        of your central heating system. Due to this reason, we don’t perform power flushes
                                        on central heating systems. </p>
                                    <p>Instead, we carry out a chemical flush. This is a highly effective and easy way to keep
                                        your system protected and it’s approved by our many manufacturing partners.</p>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_21" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        What is a plume management kit?
                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_21" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>A plume management kit directs any 'products of combustion' away from the various openings
                                        or vents into your property. This is a crucial element of your central heating system
                                        and works to keep you and your family safe.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Delivery &amp; Installation</h3>
                        <div class="panel panel-default  faq-section-panels">
                            <div class="panel-heading">
                                <h4 class="panel-title">
                                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2_22" class="btn-accordion collapsed">
                                        Will 24|7 Staywarm take my old boiler?

                                    </a>
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div id="collapse2_22" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>We will always dispose of any old materials including your old boiler unless you tell
